    "Similarly, in the 'Offensive' category, our model attained a score of 0.95, significantly higher than the baseline scores of 0.27 and 0.35, respectively.",
    "Even in the 'Provocative' category, which often contains more subtle and nuanced language, our FAST-RNN model reached a score of 0.91, outperforming the baseline's 0.61 and 0.59.",
